6.00	The_Blue_Eagle_At_Work	The Blue Eagle At Work	The title of the book refers to the symbol adopted by the National Recovery Administration. The National Industrial Recovery Act was enacted by Congress in 1933 to stimulate the American economy and help the nation recover from the Great Depression. The law created the NRA to administer the act. Section 7(a) of the Act promoted the formation of labor unions, and created a tremendous upsurge of union organizing.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3b/NewDealNRA.jpg/150px-NewDealNRA.jpg
